<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-52-1109 </DOCNO><TEXT>An account of Greece's energy industry. Lignite remains the most importantenergy reserve and accounts for more than 60% of electricity generation.The Public Power Corporation (PPC) is introducing incentive schemes toimprove the output and quality of lignite. The main objective is to reduceenergy imports and maximise domestic energy sources such as lignite,hydro, geothermal and renewables. Presently, the cement industry is themajor importer of steam coal. PPC, which has so far enjoyed the monopolyof power production and distribution, will now be challenged by smallprivate independent producers. The ministry of energy has announced thetariffs that PPC will have to pay independents who wish to sell powerto PPC. 2 figs., 2 tabs.</TEXT></DOC>